SATIRE 8. This satire is a report made by Fundanius, one of Horace' s friendS‚ of a dinner given by a mil· lionaire of the time to Maecenas and some of his friends, Although the host evidently is depicted as having more money than hrains, yet it is not merely the ostentation of the parvenu that is satirized, but the misplaced diligence of the epicure (cf. 11. 2. and 4). Nor must we suppose that every fact stated is to be taken as ludicrous any more than in Sat. 11. The piece is only a narrative, οξ which parts are satiri· cal, parts are humorous incident, and parts again merely the neces- sary detail to make a picture.
